==Scots==

===Etymology===
Vartiant of the Scots word ''[[lawlands]]'' meaning [[lowlands]] of [[Scotland]].

===Noun===
'''Lallans'''

# the [[Scots]] language, a Germanic language closely related to English and descended from northern dialects of Old English, spoken in parts of Scotland; in particular the south, central and [[Doric]] dialects.
# [[English]] spoken with a [[Scots]] accent and using [[Gaelic]] loan words.

